rComments: The pop culture course was weird. It was 12 weeks of analyzing dense academic articles. Prof. McLeod basically put all of the work on the students to "present" and he would periodically jump in and talk for five minutes. It's gotta be the laziest form of "teaching" I've ever seen. I got a good grade but I nearly lost my mind - it was that boring.
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Genius, for real...really makes u think about pop culture. When he's in a good mood, we breathe a little easier...after the first week, everyone sat away from him but we really enjoyed class. take detailed notes during lecture, and add some notes from the text. exam was really hard and long, but pretty fair. i'm gonna take another course with him!
Really smart prof, good teacher...makes class fun...but OMG he's so moody! don't come late and don't interrupt him or he'll ream you. jus study the text book and you're good to go...paper was brutal

Took the course in 1st year thinking it would be boring. Was surprised! One of the most INSPIRING profs I've ever had. He is a genius but makes it a point to teach you how to listen to and analyze music. My friends and I look for courses taught by him (very rare). He uses videos, jokes and examples from movies and tv to help us learn better.
